    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Kislev (December)</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">(English note)</p>
            <p>(Hebrew)</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">For the sake of my brother and friend I<lb/> seek peace for my
                beloved friend, etc, <addressee>Isaac</addressee><lb/> of the house of
                    <addressee>Leeser</addressee>. Although our sages said,<lb/> “Where there is no
                man present, try to be a man,”<lb/> nevertheless I never expected to stand in
                the<lb/> place of the great, but for the honor of the Torah<lb/> I cannot shut my
                eyes to the poor man whose<lb/> lips drip water from the wells of the Torah. Now
                I<lb/> sent a letter to you, my friend, about <persName>Rabbi<lb/>
                    Gershom</persName>, who has taken refuge under the<lb/> wings of the eagle of
                this land because of<lb/> the bitter lot of the Jews in the land of his<lb/> birth.
                This scholar is casting about everywhere<lb/> like a blind man in midday to
                find<lb/> a means of livelihood for his household<lb/> who depend upon him, as I
                have explained<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to you in my former letter. I therefore<lb/> hope you will not shut your ear to<lb/>
                this plea and will publish this matter<lb/> in your magazine. Perhaps a
                position<lb/> will be found for him in this way. I<lb/> am not the one to pass on
                him, but the<lb/> great scholars of our time have<lb/> already testified in regard
                to him<lb/> and his knowledge that he is a<lb/> thoroughly acquainted with all
                the<lb/> secrets of the Talmud and the com–<lb/>mentators. It is only because of
                the<lb/> honor of the Torah that I cannot<lb/> contain myself. The seeker after
                the<lb/> good of his brother—<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon Cohen <del>Nuht</del><lb/> Noot</persName></p>
        </body>
